Load Biogeme parameters

bio_results <- here("models",
                    "mode-ind-choice",
                    "biogeme_parameters_mode_ind.csv") |>
  read_csv(show_col_types = FALSE) |>
  rename(Parameter = `...1`) |>
  mutate(sig = case_when(`Rob. p-value` < 0.001 ~ "***",
                         `Rob. p-value` < 0.01 ~ "**",
                         `Rob. p-value` < 0.05 ~ "*",
                         TRUE ~ ""))

Load predictions

sim_data <- here("data",
                 "sim-data.csv") |>
  read_csv(show_col_types = FALSE)

predictions <- here("models",
                    "mode-ind-choice",
                    "biogeme_preds_mode_ind.csv") |>
  read_csv(show_col_types = FALSE) |>
  cbind(sim_data) 

test <- predictions |>
  filter(vary == "age") |>
  select(c(starts_with("Prob. "), 
           age)) |>
  pivot_longer(cols = -age,
               names_to = "alt",
               values_to = "prob") |>
  group_by(age) |>
  summarise(total_p = sum(prob))

Visualizations

mode_ind_pal <- c("#e0deed",
                  "#a29cc9",
                  "#f3fad1",
                  "#dcf174",
                  "#b1d115",
                  "#dcf1da",
                  "#96d491",

fn_plot_preds_c <- function(my_preds,
                          to_vary) {
  my_preds |>
    filter(vary == to_vary) |>
    select(c(matches(to_vary), starts_with("Prob. "))) |>
    pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("Prob. "),
                 names_to = "Mode",
                 values_to = "Probability",
                 names_prefix = "Prob. ") |>
    mutate(Mode = factor(Mode, 
                         levels = c("alone walk",
                                    "alone bike",
                                    "mom car",
                                    "mom walk",
                                    "mom bike",
                                    "mom and dad car",
                                    "mom and dad walk",
                                    "mom and dad bike",
                                    "dad car",
                                    "dad walk",
                                    "dad bike",
                                    "non-hh car",
                                    "non-hh walk",
                                    "non-hh bike",
                                    "sibling car",
                                    "sibling walk",
                                    "sibling bike"),
                         labels = c("Walk alone",
                                    "Bike alone",
                                    "Car with mom",
                                    "Walk with mom",
                                    "Bike with mom",
                                    "Car with mom and dad",
                                    "Walk with mom and dad",
                                    "Bike with mom and dad",
                                    "Car with dad",
                                    "Walk with dad",
                                    "Bike with dad",
                                    "Car with a non-household member",
                                    "Walk with a non-household member",
                                    "Bike with a non-household member",
                                    "Car with a sibling",
                                    "Walk with a sibling",
                                    "Bike with a sibling"))) |>
    rename(to_vary = !!to_vary) |>
    ggplot() +
    geom_area(aes(x = to_vary,
                  y = Probability,
                  fill = Mode)) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = mode_ind_pal) +
    theme_minimal() +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0, 0.5, 1),
                       labels = c("0", "50%", "100%")) 
}

fn_plot_preds_b <- function(my_preds,
                          to_vary) {
  my_preds |>
    filter(vary == to_vary) |>
    select(c(matches(to_vary), starts_with("Prob. "))) |>
    pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("Prob. "),
                 names_to = "Mode",
                 values_to = "Probability",
                 names_prefix = "Prob. ") |>
    mutate(Mode = factor(Mode, 
                         levels = c("alone walk",
                                    "alone bike",
                                    "mom car",
                                    "mom walk",
                                    "mom bike",
                                    "mom and dad car",
                                    "mom and dad walk",
                                    "mom and dad bike",
                                    "dad car",
                                    "dad walk",
                                    "dad bike",
                                    "non-hh car",
                                    "non-hh walk",
                                    "non-hh bike",
                                    "sibling car",
                                    "sibling walk",
                                    "sibling bike"),
                         labels = c("Walk alone",
                                    "Bike alone",
                                    "Car with mom",
                                    "Walk with mom",
                                    "Bike with mom",
                                    "Car with mom and dad",
                                    "Walk with mom and dad",
                                    "Bike with mom and dad",
                                    "Car with dad",
                                    "Walk with dad",
                                    "Bike with dad",
                                    "Car with a non-household member",
                                    "Walk with a non-household member",
                                    "Bike with a non-household member",
                                    "Car with a sibling",
                                    "Walk with a sibling",
                                    "Bike with a sibling"))) |>
    rename(to_vary = !!to_vary) |>
    ggplot() +
    geom_col(aes(x = as_factor(to_vary),
                  y = Probability,
                  fill = Mode),
             position = "stack") +
    scale_fill_manual(values = mode_ind_pal) +
    theme_minimal() +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0, 0.5, 1),
                       labels = c("0", "50%", "100%")) 
}

  scale_x_continuous(name = "Child's age")
